e $\\kappa$ cannot be constrained for groups T1 and T2 and is\n-2.4$\\pm0.3$ for group T3 and -1.6$\\pm0.3$ for group T4. We confirmed the\nrelationship of a decreasing trend in binary fractions towards late-type stars.\nNo correlation between the spectral type and the orbital period distribution\nhas been found yet, possibly due to the limitation of observational cadence.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 20 Sep 2021 18:08:02 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 24 Nov 2021 00:53:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-02-16"}
